references.paper_title: Hierarchical text-conditional image generation with CLIP latents
references.reason: This paper introduces a foundational text-to-image generation model that is directly relevant to the core methodology of ColJailBreak.

references.paper_title: High-resolution image synthesis with latent diffusion models
references.reason: This paper details Stable Diffusion, a key model used in ColJailBreak and a widely used text-to-image generation model that the paper analyzes.
This paper introduces SAM, a powerful image segmentation model that is crucial for ColJailBreak's editing phase.

references.paper_title: Photorealistic text-to-image diffusion models with deep language understanding
references.reason: This paper introduces DALL-E 2, another crucial model in ColJailBreak and a widely used text-to-image generation model that is analyzed in the paper.

references.paper_title: Learning transferable visual models from natural language supervision
references.reason: This paper introduces CLIP, a model that is fundamental to many text-to-image models and is used in ColJailBreak's collaborative optimization.
